data.enText: (especially in the past) a person on a ship who attacks other ships at sea in order to steal from them
a person who makes illegal copies of video tapes, computer programs, books, etc., in order to sell them
a person or an organization that broadcasts illegally
to copy and use or sell sb's work or a product without permission and without having the right to do so

tr: a ship that is manned by pirates
someone who robs at sea or plunders the land from the sea without having a commission from any sovereign nation
someone who uses another person's words or ideas as if they were his own

example: The Cubans commandeered the plane and flew it to Miami

value.def: Pirates are sailors who attack other ships and steal property from them.

example.ex: In the nineteenth century, pirates roamed the seas.

value.def: You can refer to someone who behaves in an immoral or illegal way as a pirate .

example.ex: Of course I knew Max was a rogue, a bit of a pirate.
example.tran: 我当然知道麦克斯是个无赖，是个小流氓。

value.def: Someone who pirates video tapes, cassettes, books, or computer programs copies and sells them when they have no right to do so.

example.ex: A school technician pirated anything from video nasties to computer games.
example.tran: 学校的一名技术人员做盗版，从黄色录像到计算机游戏什么都有。

example.ex: ...American manufacturers who've seen their designs pirated in other countries.
example.tran: 见过自己的设计在其他国家遭到盗版的美国制造商

value.tran: 非法复制及出售（录像带、录音带、书籍、计算机程序等）

example.ex: Pirated copies of music tapes are flooding the market...
example.tran: 盗版音乐带正充斥市场。

example.ex: A pirated edition of the book was published in August 1986.
example.tran: 这本书的一个盗版版本在1986年8月出版。

value.def: A pirate version of something is an illegal copy of it.

example.ex: Pirate copies of the video are already said to be in Britain.
example.tran: 该录像带的盗版版本据说已在英国出现。

trans: 海盗纸牌接龙；海盗接龙
